g.text: You: Try to pull the door apart.
Inland Empire: This isn't gonna work without the lieutenant here. What if you *do* find a way in and it's a *trap*? Kitsuragi needs to be here, covering you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "...and it's right here! A maintenance door." He points to a rusted metal double door to the right of the pipe, obscured by the reeds.
Visual Calculus: He means: the pipe must be coming from *somewhere* in the building.
Physical Instrument: The metal doors are heavy, and very awkward to open on your own, but you just manage to slide them open wide enough for you to slide yourself between them...
The metal doors are heavy and the flaking rust hurts your palms, but, together with the lieutenant, you manage to slide them open just enough to squeeze in.
Drainage Pipe: And? And nothing. Broken glass from bottles thrown against the walls of the pipe. A syringe...
You: Come closer and look in.
Physical Instrument: You can't seem to pry the doors apart for long enough to slip through. A second pair of hands would be really useful here.
You: "This looks like a great place to stash narcotics. I want to make sure there's nothing hidden in there that children might pick up."
Physical Instrument: It looks too exhausting to even try. You'd only bloody your fingers on the rust.
Perception (Smell): A very, very faint smell of stale liquor still lingers -- or is it just your imagination?
Kim Kitsuragi: "However, the pipe suggests there may be an entrance to the basement around..." The lieutenant pushes aside the reeds and looks around.
Drainage Pipe: Your eyes slowly begin to adjust to the darkness inside the drainage pipe.
Drainage Pipe: Behind the pipe -- the maintenance door, rusted shut and half-sunken in sand.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant leans back against the door, panting. "Let's take a breather and try this again later? It's... very tough."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks over your shoulder.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I see. Another stop on your crusade against narcomania. I *was* hoping we were in pursuit of a murder suspect..."
You: Could I get into the Feld building through this pipe?
"Could we get into the Feld building through this pipe?"
Drainage Pipe: An old pipe peeks out from beneath the rotting boards of the boardwalk. Could this be an alternative path into the Feld building?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Given that this isn't a martial arts thriller," a grin flickers across his face, "it's highly unlikely -- and not without risk to our health either."
Logic: Oh, duh, why didn't you think of that?
Interfacing: It's jammed shut. The subtle approach isn't going to work on this one.
Inland Empire: This isn't gonna work without the lieutenant here. What if you *do* find a way in and it's a *trap*? Kitsuragi needs to be here, covering you.
Physical Instrument: You and the lieutenant lean all your weight into pushing the doors apart, but you're not quite synchronized in your efforts. They slam shut again before you can enter.
Drainage Pipe: An ordinary drainage pipe. Darkness.
At first, you can't make anything out in the darkness at all.
The pipe is sleek with rain.
A thin layer of snow gleams inside the pipe.
Suggestion: The lieutenant's face lights up. He doesn't usually notice these little things.
Endurance: Oh yeah... *big boy time*. This needs you to put your BACK into it.
Visual Calculus: A building like this must have multiple doors serving various functions. Perhaps a basement access?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good work." The lieutenant nods toward the impenetrable darkness inside. "Shall we?"
Drainage Pipe: As your eyes adjust, you see some trash -- crumpled up newspapers, cigarette butts. Someone has half-heartedly spray-painted 'SKULLS' on the right side.
